Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe welcomed President Trump and First Lady Melania as the first state guests in the Reiwa era. Abe emphasized the strong bond between the US and Japan, particularly in terms of peace and security. He expressed hope for the resolution of the abduction issue with North Korea and stated that he is willing to meet with Chairman Kim Jong Un directly. Abe also highlighted the progress in US-Japan cooperation in areas such as energy, digital, and infrastructure. President Trump praised the US-Japan alliance and expressed optimism for a trade deal with Japan. He also mentioned the ongoing negotiations with China and his belief that Iran wants to make a deal. Trump downplayed North Korea's recent missile launches and criticized former Vice President Joe Biden. Both leaders emphasized the importance of peace and stability in the region.